## Common anti-patterns (reviewers reject these)

| Anti-pattern | Why it's wrong |
|---|---|
| `http.Get(url)` / `requests.get(url)` / `fetch(url)` in hot paths | New client per call -> no keepalive -> handshake tax per request |
| Default OS TCP keepalive in cloud | 2-hour idle means dead-peer detection happens long after the LB cut |
| `keepalive > load balancer idle timeout` | LB wins; "random" disconnects appear in P99 |
| Renumbering a protobuf field | Wire-incompatible; corrupts every existing serialized message |
| Removing a protobuf field without `reserved` | Sets up the next change to silently reuse the number and corrupt data |
| Scalar field for true optional semantics in proto3 | Default-value doesn't serialize; receiver can't distinguish set-to-zero from absent |
| gRPC as a browser-callable public API without Connect / gRPC-Web | Doesn't work; teams discover too late |
| Stripping unknown protobuf fields in middleware | Destroys forward compatibility |
| One protobuf file with everything | Hard to evolve; circular imports |
| `rev: nightly` or `rev: main` on protobuf-related pre-commit hooks | Mutable references; pin to a release tag |

---

## Reviewer checklist

For HTTP / gRPC client code:

- [ ] Client / channel created once (package-level, DI, singleton) and reused
- [ ] Explicit timeout set (overall request, not just connect)
- [ ] TCP keepalive interval set, less than load balancer idle timeout
- [ ] Pool size (`MaxIdleConnsPerHost` etc.) sized to workload, not left at default
- [ ] TLS minimum is 1.2; prefer 1.3
- [ ] Retry policy bounded (max attempts, max total time, exponential backoff with jitter)
- [ ] Metrics emitted: latency histogram, status counter, connection-reuse ratio

For `.proto` changes:

- [ ] No field renumbered (verified by `buf breaking`)
- [ ] Removed fields have `reserved` for both number AND name
- [ ] New fields use unused numbers (never reused)
- [ ] Optional semantics use `optional` keyword or wrapper types, not scalar defaults
- [ ] Package is version-suffixed (`org.domain.vN`)
- [ ] `buf breaking` runs in CI against the merge base
- [ ] Generated code policy is consistent (committed XOR generated in CI; not both)

For long-lived connections (WebSocket / SSE / gRPC streaming):

- [ ] Application-level heartbeat every 30-60s
- [ ] Reconnect logic with exponential backoff + jitter
- [ ] Idle timeout configured at every proxy in the path (or smallest-wins documented)

